      <!-- Hero -->
      <section class="hero" id="hero">
        <div class="ambient" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="mist" style="top:15%; left:25%; animation-delay:1s;"></div>
          <div class="mist" style="top:50%; left:70%; animation-delay:4s;"></div>
          <div class="mist" style="top:75%; left:40%; animation-delay:7s;"></div>
        </div>

        <h1>Prague</h1>
        <div class="subtitle">
          A city where Gothic spires meet riverside hush, and time appears in layered cobblestones.
          Prague is equal parts story and secret.
        </div>
        <div class="quote">
          “Prague is the storybook that wrote itself in stone.” <small>— Local whisper</small>
        </div>
        <div class="quote">
          “In alley light and river fog, every turn feels like a secret kept for you.” <small>— Traveler’s note</small>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Best Time to Visit -->
      <section class="section" id="best-time">
        <h2>Best Time to Visit</h2>
        <div class="desc">
          There isn’t a single “right” season—Prague shifts like a living mosaic. Winters are quiet
          and misty, spring unfurls blossoms over castles, summers pulse with festivals and crowds,
          and autumn paints the riverbanks in amber. For first-time visitors, late spring or early
          autumn balance mild light, manageable crowds, and that lingering, slightly nostalgic
          atmosphere. 
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="max-width:850px; margin:0 auto; display:flex; gap:20px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
          <div style="flex:1; min-width:220px;">
            <div class="label">Why First-Timers</div>
            <h3 style="margin-top:0; font-size:1.35rem;">Soft light & breathing room</h3>
            <p>
              Late spring awakens the city without overwhelming it; early fall adds a golden hush
              so every corner feels both alive and intimate.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div style="flex:1; min-width:220px;">
            <div class="label">Local Truth</div>
            <h3 style="margin-top:0; font-size:1.35rem;">Seasons with stories</h3>
            <p>
              Prague’s mood changes with weather—each visit writes a new chapter. Come back in
              winter for foggy quiet, or summer for street festivals.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

